snippet.title: Home Courts With Quavo | Trailer
snippet.description: In this special, Quavo is hitting the basketball courts of Atlanta to find out what makes local communities tick. Hes joined by Renee Montgomery, Killer Mike, Walter Stith and more to discuss whats giving people hope - and more importantly, what needs to change. Dont miss it!

snippet.title: From The Streets To The NBA | Home Courts With Quavo
snippet.description: Quavos in Bankhead talking to Atlanta Celtics GM, Coach Hulio Smith and how hes managed to coach 27 guys from the streets into the NBA. He also talks to Rashaad Carruth, a former McDonalds All-American and graduate of Coach Smiths program whose son is now a member of the Celtics team.

snippet.title: Playing Hoops With Josh Smith & Chris Allen| Home Courts With Quavo
snippet.description: Quavos a long-time fan of former NBA player Josh Smith and former Michigan State Player Chris Allen - and now hes playing pool and shooting hoops with them, talking about how Josh went straight from high school to the pros, and how Chris slipped out of the leagues.

snippet.title: Quavo hangs with Melissa Proctor, Atlanta Hawks| Home Courts With Quavo
snippet.description: Quavos hanging with Melissa Proctor, the CMO of the Atlanta Hawks, talking about how the Hawks are a civic asset; how they give back to the community with things like COVID testing centers and in-house voting and how theyve helped shrink truancy.

snippet.title: Mayor Andrew Young & The Atlanta Olympics | Home Courts With Quavo
snippet.description: Quavos with former Atlanta Mayor Andrew Young - discussing his relationship with basketball and how he helped steer the Olympics to Atlanta that ultimately helped create an independent black culture in the area.
